This article is a list of the [[List of U.S. states|U.S. states]], with [[population]], [[murder]]s and [[nonnegligent manslaughter|non-negligent manslaughter]], murders, [[Gun violence in the United States|gun murders]], and [[gun ownership]] percentage, then calculated rates per 100,000. The population data is from the [[United States Census Bureau|U.S. Census Bureau]]. Murder rates were calculated based on the [[FBI]] [[Uniform Crime Reports]] and the estimated 2019 population of each state.
The 2019 U.S. population total was 328.2 million.<ref name="Population">{{Cite web|url=https://www.census.gov/data/datasets/time-series/demo/popest/2010s-state-total.html|title=State Population Totals: 2010-2019|last=Annual Estimates of the Resident Population for the United States, Regions, States, and Puerto Rico: April 1, 2010 to July 1, 2019|first=US Census Bureau|date=December 16, 2021|website=www.census.gov|language=en-US|access-date=2022-06-22}}</ref> The 2019 U.S. overall murder and non-negligent manslaughter rate per 100,000 inhabitants was 5.0.<ref name="Crime">{{Cite news|url=https://ucr.fbi.gov/crime-in-the-u.s/2019/crime-in-the-u.s.-2019/topic-pages/tables/table-4|title=Crime in the United States by Region, Geographic Division, and State, 2018–2019|last=Department of Justice|first=Federal Bureau of Investigation|date=September 2020|work=Crime in the United States, 2019|access-date=2022-06-22|language=en-US}}</ref>

